<paragraph blockId="41.[163,1072,696,1010]" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">
R e c o g n i t i o n 
<taxonomicName box="[389,595,696,717]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="djaouak">
<emphasis box="[389,595,696,717]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Ammophila djaouak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a gastral apex without metallic shine, the mesothoracic venter not prominent anteriorly and the episternal sulcus extending to the anteroventral margin of the pleuron. The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[668,798,754,776]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hemilauta">
<emphasis box="[668,798,754,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. hemilauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1044,754,776]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="djaouak">
<emphasis box="[934,1044,754,776]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. djaouak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the inner margin of the mandible with two subapical teeth and no basal tooth, the labrum with a spine on the anterior margin and the shape of the gonostyle (
<figureCitation box="[932,1019,813,835]" captionStart="Figs 398-413" captionStartId="161.[163,203,1487,1507]" captionTargetBox="[165,1070,230,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-1@161.[163,1070,204,1467]" captionTargetPageId="161" captionText="Figs 398-413: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341203/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 398</figureCitation>
) and the penis valve (
<figureCitation box="[332,425,842,864]" captionStart="Figs 444-460" captionStartId="164.[163,203,1430,1450]" captionTargetBox="[178,1060,219,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-1@164.[163,1060,196,1409]" captionTargetPageId="164" captionText="Figs 444-460: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341209/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Figs 460</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[436,475,842,864]" captionStart="Figs 563-596" captionStartId="171.[163,203,1479,1499]" captionTargetBox="[174,1070,224,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-1@171.[163,1070,204,1459]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="Figs 563-596: male genitalia: penis valve in apical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341224/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">578</figureCitation>
) (
<taxonomicName box="[499,611,842,863]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="djaouak">
<emphasis box="[499,611,842,863]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. djaouak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has one subapical tooth on the inner margin of the mandible and one blunt basal tooth, and the labrum has no spine). The male of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albotomentosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. albotomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[447,558,901,922]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="djaouak">
<emphasis box="[447,558,901,922]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. djaouak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the clypeus less elongate (
<figureCitation box="[932,1021,900,922]" captionStart="Figs 216-226" captionStartId="148.[163,203,1455,1475]" captionTargetBox="[171,1041,209,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-1@148.[163,1070,204,1434]" captionTargetPageId="148" captionText="Figs 216-226: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341177/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 225</figureCitation>
), the thorax covered with dense appressed silvery setae that obscure the underlying sculpture and in characteristically shaped gonostyle (
<figureCitation box="[628,720,959,981]" captionStart="Figs 374-389" captionStartId="159.[163,203,1499,1519]" captionTargetBox="[179,1065,225,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-1@159.[163,1070,204,1479]" captionTargetPageId="159" captionText="Figs 374-389: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341199/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 385</figureCitation>
) and penis valve (
<figureCitation box="[928,1020,959,981]" captionStart="Figs 444-460" captionStartId="164.[163,203,1430,1450]" captionTargetBox="[178,1060,219,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-1@164.[163,1060,196,1409]" captionTargetPageId="164" captionText="Figs 444-460: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341209/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 456</figureCitation>
) (
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="djaouak">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">A. djaouak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a thorax with appressed silvery setae that not obscure the underlying sculpture).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[163,1071,1026,1545]" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">
D e s c r i p t i o n 3: 
<quantity box="[419,547,1026,1048]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.075" metricValueMax="2.15" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="424" unit="mm" value="20.75" valueMax="21.5" valueMin="20.0">20-21.5 mm</quantity>
. Gastral apex without metallic shine, mesothoracic venter not prominent anteriorly, episternal sulcus extending to anteroventral margin of pleuron, arolia large and claws without basal tooth. Black, with following yellowishbrown: mandible (except apex), tegula, fore- and midlegs (except coxa), hindfemur apically, hindtibia (except apically), petiole (dorsally darkened), tergum I (except for black dorsal stripe) and remaning areas of gaster (except some dark spots). Head, thorax and propodeum covered with appressed silvery setae that do not obscure sculpture on pronotal collar, scutum and metanotum; erect setae whitish. Inner margin of mandible with one subapical tooth and one blunt basal tooth; supra-antennal lamellate projection slightly developed. Ventral margin of clypeus elongate, narrowed and emarginated medially (
<figureCitation box="[267,358,1318,1340]" captionStart="Figs 216-226" captionStartId="148.[163,203,1455,1475]" captionTargetBox="[171,1041,209,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-1@148.[163,1070,204,1434]" captionTargetPageId="148" captionText="Figs 216-226: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341177/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 226</figureCitation>
), disk concave on ventral half and convex on dorsal half (
<figureCitation box="[968,1058,1318,1340]" captionStart="Figs 332-356" captionStartId="157.[163,203,1391,1411]" captionTargetBox="[170,1049,224,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-1@157.[163,1070,204,1371]" captionTargetPageId="157" captionText="Figs 332-356: male clypeus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341195/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 341</figureCitation>
), labrum anteriorly armed with preapical spine. Pronotal collar slightly punctate, not transversely ridged. Scutum distinctly transversely punctato-rugose, scutellum punctate and longitudinally striate. Propodeal enclosure irregularly coarsely rugose, covered with sparse appressed silvery setae and with erect setae. Genitalia characteristically shaped: gonostyle laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[375,467,1465,1487]" captionStart="Figs 398-413" captionStartId="161.[163,203,1487,1507]" captionTargetBox="[165,1070,230,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-1@161.[163,1070,204,1467]" captionTargetPageId="161" captionText="Figs 398-413: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341203/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 399</figureCitation>
; penis valve laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[715,807,1465,1487]" captionStart="Figs 461-470" captionStartId="165.[163,203,1486,1506]" captionTargetBox="[173,1055,225,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-1@165.[163,1070,204,1466]" captionTargetPageId="165" captionText="Figs 461-470: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341211/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 462</figureCitation>
, ventrally: 
<figureCitation box="[932,1022,1465,1487]" captionStart="Figs 509-526" captionStartId="168.[163,203,1359,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1070,204,1315]" captionTargetId="figure-1@168.[163,1070,204,1339]" captionTargetPageId="168" captionText="Figs 509-526: male genitalia: penis valve in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341218/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 521</figureCitation>
and apically: 
<figureCitation box="[260,351,1494,1516]" captionStart="Figs 563-596" captionStartId="171.[163,203,1479,1499]" captionTargetBox="[174,1070,224,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-1@171.[163,1070,204,1459]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="Figs 563-596: male genitalia: penis valve in apical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341224/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="424">Fig. 580</figureCitation>
. Sternum VIII slightly emarginate. Flagellomere I: II=1.7; length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+II+0.3×III.
</paragraph>
